This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with graph matching, which is a common problem in computer vision and pattern recognition. The use of linear function spaces and geometric insights also suggests a focus on computer vision. It is also likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as the proposed method involves optimization and parameterization. The use of functional representation and optimization strategy also suggests a focus on data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG).
